Kisii county secretary and Public Service boss Patrick Lumumba on Friday said they are ready to receive Cuban doctors. He said they have renovated houses for the expats. “We’ve done all the necessary arrangements to receive the two Cuban doctors in our county,” Lumumba said in his office. The county has also assigned two vehicles to be used to be used by the medics — a surgeon and family doctor. They will serve in all subcounty hospitals at different times, Lumumba said. He said services will improve once they are deployed. A schedule will be released to residents about the facilities the doctors will serving each week. Lumumba urged residents to take advantage of the opporutnity to get help.  